						<summary>

						<p>This records some provision (not mentioned) made by <hi rend="bold">Parāśaraṉ Tāyaṉ Śāttaṉ</hi> a member of the <hi rend="italic">āḷuṅgaṇam</hi> of Kiḷinallūr a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Ōymā-nāḍu for (a special) offering of 4 <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> of rice during worship on the <hi rend="italic">amāvāsyā</hi> and <hi rend="italic">sankrānti</hi> days in the temple of Tiruvagnīśvaram-Uḍaiyār at the place, in additions to the usual daily offerings during the three services.</p>						

						</summary>
